{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I can't imagine why anyone would want to legalize drugs. It's basically like legalizing prostitution."}
{'text': "If we're going to legalize them, we should legalize gambling as well. If we legalize gambling, we'll also have to legalize prostitution, pornography, and alcohol."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we're going to legalize drugs, we should legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling as well. That way we won't be forced to give these things up."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 First of all, if you want to make a change, the easiest way is to educate yourself.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The prohibition of drugs is an anachronistic approach.'}
{'text': "It's good that we are trying to legalize drugs, but if we do, we need to establish a strict set of regulations on the market to ensure that the drug supply is tightly controlled."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we legalize porn, gambling, pornography, prostitution, and all other forms of pornography? Wouldn't this be a much better solution than legalization of drugs?"}
{'text': 'The people who have already been harmed by drug abuse (i.e. poor people, children, etc) will be disproportionately affected by legalization.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Perhaps legalizing drugs is a good thing, but we shouldn't forget that there is a bigger issue at stake here."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Many of the drugs that are legally available today are often abused.'}
{'text': 'You really want to legalize drugs? I guess I can see why. It would be great if we could get away from the war on drugs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I agree with the argument that legalization of drugs can lead to more people using drugs. However, I also think it's important to maintain strict control over the supply of drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's say that there were fewer drugs in the market. It would mean that no one would invest in those drugs, so they wouldn't be available for use."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you do legalize drugs, we'll still need to deal with all the potential problems these drugs could potentially cause, such as the potential for drug cartels to spring up and start selling drugs..."}
{'text': '2. Legalizing Drugs Will Increase Crime.'}

{'text': 'There is no comparison between marijuana and heroin. They are completely different drugs with completely different effects. You cannot compare them to one another. They are two completely different substances.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's very important to note several things here. First of all, it's important to realize that the actual legalization of drugs would not change the fact that drugs are illegal."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's make sure that the drugs that are legalized are not also heavily taxed. If the drug is heavily taxed, the amount of people who abuse it will only increase."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that legalization of drugs is the best way to go about this."}
{'text': 'The current policy of prohibition is not the only possible solution to the problem of drug addiction.'}

{'text': 'In a free society, no one should have to ask for permission from the government to engage in any activity. That would lead to anarchy, and no one would be able to control their own actions.'}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs will mean more people will die. For every person killed by a drug overdose, many more people will be murdered or maimed by gangs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we're going to end up with a large number of people addicted to the drug. This will lead to an increased number of drug users."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't like the idea of legalization. I think it would lead to more drug abuse and criminal activity. The U.S."}
{'text': 'Legalizing drugs will lead to an increase in drug use. In my opinion, this is a good thing.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Regardless of whether or not we should legalize drugs, we should at least legalize prostitution, pornography, gambling, and homosexuality.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize something, people will find a way of getting around the law. In the case of prostitution, it is very easy for a person to do so.'}
{'text': "There are many people who become addicted to drugs because their parents aren't there to prevent them from doing so."}
{'text': "By legalizing drugs, we're also legalizing alcohol and tobacco. By legalizing drugs, we'll also be legalizing prostitution, pornography, gambling, and other forms of vice."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Maybe our society is too complacent and lazy to deal with the problem of drug abuse and crime.'}
{'text': "Legalization would be the best thing that could happen to us, as a society. There's no reason to be fighting against things like drug abuse and prostitution."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It'll be hard to maintain a strictly controlled market, especially when there won't be a central authority in charge of controlling sales."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we want to legalize drugs, we need to legalize prostitution as well. After all, they are two very similar practices. They both involve sex, use, and abuse.'}
{'text': "It's about time that we get the message across that there is a significant difference between marijuana, heroin, and opiates."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Don't legalize drugs for recreational purposes, just legalize it for medicinal purposes. It's too bad that the United States has made the mistake of legalizing drugs for recreational purposes."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We need to regulate the manufacture and sale of drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is no evidence that states with legalized drugs have significantly lower drug use rates than states with illegal drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The problem of drug abuse and crime has been with us for a long time, and if we were to legalize drugs, we would probably end up with a larger number of people addicted to...'}
{'text': 'If we are going to legalize drugs, why not legalize prostitution as well? If prostitution is legalized as well, there will be no reason to continue using drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It might be a good idea to legalize prostitution as well. After all, they are both similar practices. They both involve sex, use, and abuse.'}
{'text': "In an ideal world, everyone would enjoy the freedom to do as they please, and we'd all be happy. But unfortunately, that is not the case."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 People who are against the legalization of drugs are being hypocritical.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Even though the legalization of drugs will lead to serious problems, I don't think it's a bad idea at all. Quite the opposite, actually."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's not legalize all drugs at the same time. Instead, let's legalize drugs like marijuana and heroin, and then let the market decide which drugs to use."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If it isn't a problem, why are we trying to make it a problem? If there aren't any problems, why are we putting so much effort into making them a problem?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The problem of drug abuse and crime has been with us for a long time, and if we were to legalize drugs, we would probably end up with a larger number of people addicted to...'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 To be honest, I don't think the thought of legalizing drugs is a bad one. I think it's a good idea."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think we should legalize drugs at all. I think we should legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling. That's a much better idea."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I feel like the overwhelming majority of people who are in favor of legalization simply do not know what they are talking about, and have never experienced the effects that drugs have on their lives.'}
{'text': 'Unfortunately, things are going to get much worse before they get better. We have no idea how many people will try drugs and end up addicted.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we'll at least reduce the level of people who abuse them."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In a way, I'm glad we don't allow people to use drugs."}
{'text': '1. Why are we trying to regulate our lives while we continue to use drugs? 2. Would it have been better for us to stop using drugs all together?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if drugs weren't legal? Would we be able to talk to each other about this?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm in favor of legalizing all of the above mentioned activities so long as they are done in a controlled manner."}
{'text': 'In the end, I think that legalization of drugs would lead to even more problems than we currently have. It could lead to a lot of people using drugs.'}
{'text': "Why are we trying to regulate each aspect of our lives while we continue to use drugs? This isn't working. In fact, it's doing very little good at all."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The legalization of drugs will likely lead to more people using drugs, which means more drug abuse and criminal activity.'}
{'text': "Wouldn't it have been better for us to stop using drugs all together? That might have had a positive effect on society as a whole."}
{'text': 'Why do we need to regulate our lives while we continue to use drugs? Why not just legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling?'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 How bad would it be if people got stoned all the time, and could go back to their normal lives whenever they wanted?'}
{'text': "Cannabis is a plant, yes. It's not a human being, even if some people believe it is."}
{'text': 'If you legalize drugs, the people who want to use drugs will find ways to smuggle them in to the country illegally.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm not going to argue that we shouldn't legalize drugs. You can't stop people from taking drugs."}

{'text': 'Legalization of drugs could lead to a more civilized society. After all, prohibition has failed miserably. Prohibition leads to more drug abuse, criminal activity, and oppression of people who use drugs.'}
{'text': 'If you really want to end addiction to drugs, you need to legalize the prostitution, pornography, and gambling industry as well.'}
{'text': "By legalizing drugs, we are also legalizing alcohol and tobacco. By legalizing drugs, we'll also be legalizing prostitution and pornography."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There's no point in trying to regulate our lives when we continue to use drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think that legalizing drugs will lead to a more civilized society."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you're going to legalize drugs, maybe you should legalize prostitution as well. Prostitution is just as much a social ill as drug abuse."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There is a difference between legalizing drugs, and legalizing the entire social structure that is based on the drug trade.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There are plenty of drugs out there that are far more dangerous than marijuana, and we should make sure that we aren't allowing anyone to get stoned any time they want."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What kind of message will it send to the next generation if we let them choose what they can and can't do with their own bodies?"}
{'text': 'If you go ahead and legalize all of the above listed activities, it will only result in more people using drugs. Not that few people will use drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we're going to end up with an increased number of drug users."}
{'text': "If we legalize drugs, we will have to spend a lot of our government's resources on legalizing drugs and that will be a tremendous waste of money."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's legalize drugs, but regulate them closely. This way, we won't have to worry about drugs being sold on the black market."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think the most important thing we need to do is to find better ways to approach the problem. Legalizing drugs is not the answer.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, we're not going to end up with a civilized society."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling as well? Wouldn't that lead to even less people getting addicted to them? Doesn't that seem logical to you?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 legalizing drugs is a slippery slope. Legalizing drugs will certainly lead to the legalization of prostitution, pornography, and all sorts of other things that aren't even illegal."}
{'text': 'Maybe our society is too complacent and lazy to deal with the issue of drug abuse and crime.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 First of all, I think it would be a terrible idea to legalize drugs. Second, I think legalizing drugs would lead to other social ills as well.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It may be possible to find a solution to the problem of drug abuse and crime by legalizing drugs.'}
{'text': "I don't know how we should legalize drugs, but let's legalize prostitution! That would be a much more productive use of our tax dollars."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I personally don't like the idea of legalizing prostitution, pornography, or gambling. I feel that it would lead to even less people getting addicted to them than it already does."}
{'text': "If we legalize drugs, we're going to end up with an increased number of drug users, which will in turn lead to an increased number of drug addicts."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's very important to realize that the current policy of prohibition is not the only possible solution to the problem of drug addiction."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Wouldn't it be better to allow people to grow their own pot? Isn't it a better alternative to legalizing drugs?"}
{'text': "The biggest problem with this whole 'legalize drugs' thing is that there's no way to enforce it once it happens."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Instead of legalizing drugs, we should legalize prostitution as well. For one thing, prostitution is an industry that thrives on the corruption of governments and corrupt police forces.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we're going to legalize drugs, we should legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling, too. That way, we won't be forced to give these things up."}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, you'll also end up legalizing prostitution, pornography, gambling, and other forms of vice."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In order to solve the problem of drugs, we need to look at the whole system that is based on the drug trade instead of focusing solely on the issue of drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We should legalize drugs for recreational purposes. That way, we won't have any more problems than we have now."}
{'text': 'The legalization of drugs would lead to more people using drugs, because there would be but more people with access to drugs (i. e. more people to buy drugs). This is bad for everyone.'}
{'text': "I honestly don't know what to say about the legalization of prostitution, pornography, gambling, and homosexuality. If they are bad for society, let's get rid of them."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It's better to legalize drugs than tolerate a society where people get addicted to drugs and go on to become criminals."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's legalize drugs until the point where drug abuse is so prevalent that it is just as harmful as alcohol and tobacco."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 For many years, the government has tried to solve the problem of drug abuse and addiction by telling people that the only way they can stop using drugs is by completely abstaining from them.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I personally feel that the legalization of drugs would lead to increased levels of drug abuse and criminal activity. I think this would be a very bad idea.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, you'll have fewer problems than you do now, and you'll have more money to spend on health care."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would lead to social ills as well.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Personally, I don't think that legalization of drugs is the answer."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 People who are addicted to drugs will, at some point, need to get off of drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Not every drug is going to be regulated.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The #1 reason for drug addiction is shame. The #2 reason is fear. The #3 reason is greed.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I'm not opposed to legalizing drugs, but I don't think it should be done at the expense of society's health, well-being, and morals."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not just stop doing drugs altogether, so that we wouldn't have to spend so much time and resources on the war on drugs in the first place?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you want to get rid of addictive drugs, legalize prostitution, pornography, and gambling instead. That way, you won't be forced to give them up."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we want to legalize drugs for recreational purposes, then we should legalize prostitution as well.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we had legalized drugs 40 years ago, when alcohol was legal, and we didn't ever see another person getting killed by drunk drivers or drunk people killing others?"}
{'text': 'What would happen if we legalized prostitution, pornography, and gambling?'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We are living in a society where many people are doing drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs doesn't solve any of the problems associated with the drug trade."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The question of whether or not to legalize drugs is not a question of whether or not to legalize marijuana or heroin.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Just because it's legal doesn't mean it has to be safe. Most things that are legal have been proven to be unsafe at times."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I personally feel that it's a good idea to legalize prostitution, pornography, gambling, and other things that have been made illegal by the government. Should we legalize these things as well?"}
{'text': "It's a good idea to legalize drugs, but it's not a good idea to legalize drugs."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The most important thing we can do to combat drug abuse is to educate people about the dangers of drug abuse. Our government seems to have no desire to do this.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalize drugs, this will lead to an increase in the number of drug addicts (i.e.'}
{'text': 'People, especially children, need to be protected from having easy access to legal substances. This is not an issue of personal freedom but an issue of public safety.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If one accepts the premise that the war on drugs has failed, then I think the next logical step would be to treat drug abuse as a public health issue rather than a criminal justice issue...'}
